reviews.review_text: WHASUP I can't believe no one has reviewed this C miller remaster of one hell of a show. Kick ass performance and sound quality. Phil thumps his ass off. Listen or download if you know how.
Well... That's because words can't describe some things.

Very Good You can tell by the Iko that Jerry was "on" for this show. First half of the 2nd set is a little short. Sorry, but LLR always brings great shows to levels of mediocrity. Nice CrazyFingers outta space. A great Stella. A very fine show.

LLR I disagree, I think Looks Like Rain is one of bobby's finest song along with Black Throated Wind. Not just bobby's best song but some of the grateful dead's best songs...Slow songs that make are always welcome in the list according to me, looks like rain, black throated wind, mission in the rain, standing on the moon, and of course so many roads.....stella blue = time for a smoke break...Well now in the furthur days

Great to hear The Iko>LLR>Terrapin>Drumz has long been a favorite of mine, and the Fingers out of space is well played.

This is one of my favorite drumz though, it goes from crazy, to tribal with Bill and Mick bringing out the hand drums.  Listen to the lady having a real good time once the talking drum comes out, she yells "I wanna fuck Jerry Garcia" 

I think the boys were really saving all their energy for the next night, which is a killer show, but this show is great too, check it out.  The first set is solid, I wouldn't say any huge highlights, but well played, but for me the second set is where it's at.
